{"id": 57867, "date": "2025-07-27T04:00:33", "date_gmt": "2025-07-27T11:00:33", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=57867"}, "modified": "2026-03-12T12:19:57", "modified_gmt": "2026-03-12T19:19:57", "slug": "kingdom-of-days-july-27-2", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/07/27/kingdom-of-days-july-27-2/", "title": {"rendered": "July 27"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p><strong>1964: </strong>Cindy Mizelle, backing vocalist on &#8220;Shackled and Drawn,&#8221; &#8220;High Hopes,&#8221; &#8220;American Skin (41 Shots),&#8221; &#8220;Just Like Fire Would,&#8221; and &#8220;Heaven&#8217;s Wall&#8221; &#8212; and of course, throughout the entire Seeger Sessions, Working on a Dream, Wrecking Ball, and High Hopes tours &#8212; is born in Englewood, New Jersey.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"3228\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/cindy/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/cindy.jpg?fit=600%2C463&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"600,463\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"cindy\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/cindy.jpg?fit=300%2C232&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/cindy.jpg?fit=600%2C463&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3228 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/cindy.jpg?resize=600%2C463&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"463\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/cindy.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/cindy.jpg?resize=300%2C232&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1970:\u00a0</strong>Bruce catches a gig by and jams with Funky Dusty and The Soul Broom (a side project of Steve, Garry, Southside, and Bobby Williams) at The Upstage in Asbury Park.</p>\n<p><strong>1973:\u00a0</strong>Bruce and his band perform at the annual CBS Sales Convention at the Fairmont Hotel in San Francisco. Bruce is asked and scheduled to play for fifteen minutes, but he plays for 40 minutes instead, overstaying his welcome and failing to impress following the special effects-laden mini-set by Edgar Winter&#8217;s White Trash.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"3230\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1973-0727/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1973-0727.jpg?fit=261%2C415&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"261,415\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1973-0727\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1973-0727.jpg?fit=189%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1973-0727.jpg?fit=261%2C415&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3230 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1973-0727.jpg?resize=261%2C415&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"261\" height=\"415\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1973-0727.jpg?w=261&amp;ssl=1 261w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1973-0727.jpg?resize=189%2C300&amp;ssl=1 189w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 261px) 100vw, 261px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1974:\u00a0</strong>Bruce and the E Street Band play two shows at the Celebrity Theater in Phoenix, netting them their biggest payday to date by far.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"19950\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1974-07-27/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?fit=1293%2C1402&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1293,1402\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1974-07-27\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?fit=277%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?fit=758%2C822&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19950 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?resize=758%2C822&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"822\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?w=1293&amp;ssl=1 1293w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?resize=277%2C300&amp;ssl=1 277w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?resize=944%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 944w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1974-07-27.png?resize=768%2C833&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1976:</strong> Incensed at manager Mike Appel&#8217;s injunction preventing him from recording new material, Bruce sues Appel for fraud, breach of trust, and undue influence. Their legal battle is only just beginning.</p>\n<p><strong>1981:\u00a0</strong>Bruce is sick, causing his scheduled River Tour show in Cincinnati to be postponed.</p>\n<p><strong>1984:</strong> The Born in the U.S.A. Tour returns to the U.S., starting with a show at the Saratoga Performing Arts Center on a very rainy night. Listen in on the soundcheck of &#8220;Who&#8217;ll Stop the Rain&#8221; below.</p>\n<div id=\"v-GhQSDpeE-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/GhQSDpeE?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"19951\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1984-07-27/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?fit=1115%2C1406&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1115,1406\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1984-07-27\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?fit=238%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?fit=758%2C956&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19951 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?resize=758%2C956&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"956\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?w=1115&amp;ssl=1 1115w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?resize=238%2C300&amp;ssl=1 238w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?resize=812%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 812w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1984-07-27.png?resize=768%2C968&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"3235\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1984-0727/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1984-0727.jpg?fit=577%2C794&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"577,794\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1984-0727\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1984-0727.jpg?fit=218%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1984-0727.jpg?fit=577%2C794&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3235 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1984-0727.jpg?resize=577%2C794&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"577\" height=\"794\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1984-0727.jpg?w=577&amp;ssl=1 577w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1984-0727.jpg?resize=218%2C300&amp;ssl=1 218w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 577px) 100vw, 577px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1988:\u00a0</strong>Bruce&#8217;s Tunnel of Love show in Oslo features the return of &#8220;Thunder Road,&#8221; not yet played on this tour. The opening songs are professionally shot and broadcast.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wByMIEn4Wfg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/03F1w6qpUq4?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>1989:\u00a0</strong>Bruce joins The Fabulous Greaseband on stage at The Headliner in Neptune, New Jersey. Listen to &#8220;Long Tall Sally,&#8221; &#8220;Under the Boardwalk,&#8221; and &#8220;Sweet Little Sixteen&#8221; below.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/a0fwM4ce1_A?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"3236\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1989-0727/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1989-0727.jpg?fit=492%2C396&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"492,396\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1989-0727\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1989-0727.jpg?fit=300%2C241&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1989-0727.jpg?fit=492%2C396&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3236 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1989-0727.jpg?resize=492%2C396&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"492\" height=\"396\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1989-0727.jpg?w=492&amp;ssl=1 492w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1989-0727.jpg?resize=300%2C241&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 492px) 100vw, 492px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>1999:\u00a0</strong>On Night Six of fifteen in the opening Meadowlands stand of the Reunion Tour&#8217;s U.S. leg, &#8220;Candy&#8217;s Room&#8221; makes its long-awaited return, absent from the set list for almost 15 years.</p>\n<div id=\"v-VtdgqsqG-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/VtdgqsqG?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"19977\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/1999-07-27/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?fit=1899%2C1753&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1899,1753\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"1999-07-27\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?fit=300%2C277&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?fit=758%2C700&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19977 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?resize=758%2C700&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"700\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?w=1899&amp;ssl=1 1899w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?resize=300%2C277&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?resize=1024%2C945&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?resize=768%2C709&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1999-07-27.png?resize=1536%2C1418&amp;ssl=1 1536w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>2003:\u00a0</strong>Night Seven of ten at Giants Stadium on the Rising Tour has an unusual opening number: &#8220;Downbound Train.&#8221; Check out the rare IEM recording of &#8220;Meeting Across the River&#8221; below.</p>\n<div id=\"v-xKaPgDtU-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/xKaPgDtU?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='h